# McRPG Ability System

## Checklist: Creating a New Ability

1. Create class in `src/main/java/us/eunoians/mcrpg/ability/impl/<skill>/`
2. Extend `McRPGAbility`, implement relevant type interfaces (`PassiveAbility`, `ActiveAbility`, `ConfigurableSkillAbility`, etc.)
3. Declare a `static final NamespacedKey` on the class
4. Register components in the constructor
5. Implement `activateAbility()`, `getSkillKey()`, `getDatabaseName()`, `getYamlDocument()`, `getAbilityEnabledRoute()`, `getDisplayItemRoute()`
6. Create a corresponding `<AbilityName>ActivateEvent` in `event/ability/<skill>/`
7. Register in `McRPGExpansion.getAbilityContent()`

## Minimal Ability Template

```java
public final class MyAbility extends McRPGAbility implements PassiveAbility, ConfigurableSkillAbility {

    public static final NamespacedKey MY_ABILITY_KEY =
        new NamespacedKey(McRPGMethods.getMcRPGNamespace(), "my_ability");

    public MyAbility(@NotNull McRPG mcRPG) {
        super(mcRPG, MY_ABILITY_KEY);
        // Components checked in priority order (lowest first). First failure stops chain.
        addActivatableComponent(SwordsComponents.HOLDING_SWORD_ACTIVATE_COMPONENT, EntityDamageByEntityEvent.class, 0);
        addActivatableComponent(MyAbilityComponents.CHANCE_CHECK_COMPONENT, EntityDamageByEntityEvent.class, 1);
    }

    @Override
    public void activateAbility(@NotNull AbilityHolder abilityHolder, @NotNull Event event) {
        EntityDamageByEntityEvent dmgEvent = (EntityDamageByEntityEvent) event; // safe: only registered for this event
        YamlDocument config = getYamlDocument();

        MyAbilityActivateEvent activateEvent = new MyAbilityActivateEvent(abilityHolder, ...);
        Bukkit.getPluginManager().callEvent(activateEvent);
        if (activateEvent.isCancelled()) return;

        // Apply effect here
    }

    @NotNull @Override public NamespacedKey getSkillKey() { return Swords.SWORDS_KEY; }
    @NotNull @Override public String getDatabaseName() { return "my_ability"; }
    @NotNull @Override public Route getAbilityEnabledRoute() { return MyConfigFile.MY_ABILITY_ENABLED; }
    @NotNull @Override public YamlDocument getYamlDocument() {
        return getPlugin().registryAccess().registry(RegistryKey.MANAGER).manager(McRPGManagerKey.FILE).getFile(FileType.SWORDS_CONFIG);
    }
    @NotNull @Override public Route getDisplayItemRoute() { return LocalizationKey.MY_ABILITY_DISPLAY_ITEM_HEADER; }
}
```

## Ability with Ready State

Some abilities require two interactions: first the player "readies" them, then a second event "activates" them.

```java
public MyReadyAbility(@NotNull McRPG mcRPG) {
    super(mcRPG, MY_READY_ABILITY_KEY);
    // Right-click to ready
    addReadyingComponent(MyComponents.READY_COMPONENT, PlayerInteractEvent.class, 0);
    // Specific action to activate (after readied)
    addActivatableComponent(MyComponents.IS_READIED_COMPONENT, BlockBreakEvent.class, 0);
    addActivatableComponent(MyComponents.ACTIVATE_COMPONENT, BlockBreakEvent.class, 1);
}

@Override
public void activateAbility(@NotNull AbilityHolder abilityHolder, @NotNull Event event) {
    abilityHolder.unreadyHolder(); // Always clear ready state first
    // Fire event, check cancel, apply effect, put on cooldown
    putHolderOnCooldown(abilityHolder);
}
```

Ready state auto-expires after ~3 seconds. `ReadyData` is shared across abilities using the same tool.

## Component Types

Three component interfaces, all registered in the constructor:

| Method | Interface | Checked via | Purpose |
|--------|-----------|-------------|---------|
| `addActivatableComponent(...)` | `EventActivatableComponent` | `shouldActivate(holder, event)` | Gate activation |
| `addReadyingComponent(...)` | `EventReadyableComponent` | `shouldReady(holder, event)` | Gate readying |
| `addCancellingComponent(...)` | `EventCancellingComponent` | `shouldCancel(holder, event)` | Cancel Bukkit event on activation |

Components within a priority chain are sorted lowest-first. The first failure (returns `false` / returns `true` for cancel) short-circuits the chain.

Static component instances go in a `<Skill>Components` or `<Ability>Components` class:

```java
// Shared across abilities in a skill
public final class SwordsComponents {
    public static final EventActivatableComponent HOLDING_SWORD_ACTIVATE_COMPONENT = (holder, event) -> {
        // check logic
    };
}
```

## Cooldown Pattern

Implement `CooldownableAbility` (included via `ConfigurableActiveAbility` and related interfaces):

```java
// Inside activateAbility(), after firing the event and checking cancellation:
putHolderOnCooldown(abilityHolder); // reads cooldown from config automatically

// The AbilityListener interface already checks cooldowns before calling activateAbility()
```

## Active-Duration Abilities

For abilities that apply an effect over time (not just at activation moment):

```java
abilityHolder.addActiveAbility(this, durationSeconds); // auto-removes after duration
// OR
abilityHolder.addActiveAbility(this);                  // manual cleanup required
abilityHolder.removeActiveAbility(this);               // call when effect ends
```

## Attribute Factory Pattern (No Reflection)

Ability state per-holder lives in `AbilityData` as `AbilityAttribute<T>` instances. **Never use reflection to instantiate attributes.** Use the factory method:

```java
// Reading an attribute from the holder
Optional<AbilityData> dataOpt = abilityHolder.getAbilityData(this);
dataOpt.ifPresent(data -> {
    Optional<AbilityTierAttribute> tierAttr = data.getAbilityAttribute(AbilityAttributeRegistry.ABILITY_TIER_ATTRIBUTE_KEY);
    tierAttr.ifPresent(attr -> {
        int tier = attr.getContent(); // typed access, no casting
    });
});
```

## Authoring an AbilityListener

New listeners implement `AbilityListener` (which extends `Listener`) and call the provided default methods:

```java
public class OnSwordAttackAbilityListener implements AbilityListener {

    @EventHandler(priority = EventPriority.MONITOR, ignoreCancelled = true)
    public void onAttack(EntityDamageByEntityEvent event) {
        if (!(event.getDamager() instanceof Player player)) return;
        activateAbilities(player.getUniqueId(), event);  // default method handles all the rest
    }
}
```

`activateAbilities()` and `readyAbilities()` handle: holder lookup, world restriction checks, loadout filtering, component validation, cooldown checks, and dispatching to `activateAbility()`.

## Registering in McRPGExpansion

```java
// In McRPGExpansion.getAbilityContent():
abilityContent.addContent(new MyAbility(mcRPG));
```

## Reference: Canonical Example

See `Bleed.java` (`ability/impl/swords/Bleed.java`) — a passive ability that:
- Registers 4 activatable components with escalating priorities
- Uses `ConfigurableSkillAbility` for config-driven enable/disable
- Reads base damage and cycles from YAML via `Route` constants
- Fires `BleedActivateEvent` and delegates to a manager on success

